1
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:08,408
♪

2
00:00:08,474 --> 00:00:11,244
Narrator: LONG AGO,
AN ALREADY EXTRAORDINARY MAN

3
00:00:11,311 --> 00:00:13,514
WISHED FOR FURTHER POWER.

4
00:00:13,614 --> 00:00:17,684
THIS MAN COULD SOAR LIKE A BIRD,
SWIM LIKE A FISH,

5
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:22,188
BREATHE LIKE A TREE,
AND MOVE LIKE A WINDING STREAM.

6
00:00:22,255 --> 00:00:25,358
BUT SUNLIGHT SPELLED HIS DOOM,

7
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:27,594
SO HE CREATED A STONE MASK.

8
00:00:29,462 --> 00:00:33,333
ONE DAY, HE WOULD
FACE THE SUN WITHOUT FEAR,

9
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:37,037
AND THEN THE WORLD
WOULD BE HIS.

10
00:00:37,103 --> 00:00:38,539
Kars: HMM.

11
00:00:42,275 --> 00:00:44,010
( wind blowing )

12
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,512
Von Stroheim: WHERE'D HE GO?

13
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:48,649
PLEASE TELL ME
KARS FELL INTO THE LAVA.

14
00:00:49,550 --> 00:00:50,483
( both yell )

15
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,719
( Kars screams )

16
00:00:52,819 --> 00:00:53,887
I'M...

17
00:00:53,954 --> 00:00:55,055
STILL ALIVE.

18
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:56,389
JoJo: ALL RIGHT.

19
00:00:56,489 --> 00:00:58,992
( Kars groaning )

20
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:02,135
MUST CREATE ARMOR...

21
00:01:02,202 --> 00:01:04,871
SOMETHING LIKE A CLAM...

22
00:01:04,905 --> 00:01:06,039
OR A CRAB...

23
00:01:06,072 --> 00:01:08,407
A BONY SHELL.

24
00:01:08,474 --> 00:01:09,475
( grunts )

25
00:01:09,543 --> 00:01:12,412
YES. MAKE ME IMPERVIOUS.

26
00:01:12,513 --> 00:01:13,847
( both gasp )

27
00:01:13,914 --> 00:01:17,183
( Kars groans )

28
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:19,252
( screams )

29
00:01:19,352 --> 00:01:21,688
IT'S NOT ENOUGH!

30
00:01:21,755 --> 00:01:24,390
JoJo: YOU DUMMY, THAT'S LAVA!

31
00:01:24,424 --> 00:01:26,392
IT'S A THOUSAND DEGREES
IN THERE!

32
00:01:26,426 --> 00:01:30,030
NOW BURN TO A CRISP,
YOU COCKY BASTARD!

33
00:01:30,096 --> 00:01:34,034
( Kars screams )

34
00:01:41,341 --> 00:01:42,509
Von Stroheim: OUCH.

35
00:01:45,378 --> 00:01:48,114
JoJo: YES. THAT DID IT.

36
00:01:48,181 --> 00:01:49,783
FINALLY.

37
00:01:49,850 --> 00:01:51,785
KARS WAS THE LAST OF THEM.

38
00:01:51,885 --> 00:01:54,521
THE PILLAR MEN ARE DEFEATED!

39
00:01:54,588 --> 00:01:57,691
‐ ( Von Stroheim gasps )
‐ ( JoJo laughing )

40
00:02:05,639 --> 00:02:07,073
( both gasp )

41
00:02:07,140 --> 00:02:08,642
Von Stroheim:
THE SHOCK OF HIS DEMISE

42
00:02:08,709 --> 00:02:10,143
TRIGGERED AN ERUPTION.

43
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:12,979
LET'S GET TO SAFETY
BEFORE WE CELEBRATE FURTHER.

44
00:02:13,046 --> 00:02:13,780
JoJo: GOOD CALL.

45
00:02:13,814 --> 00:02:16,482
HANG ON TIGHT, ALL RIGHT?

46
00:02:25,959 --> 00:02:27,327
GUHH!

47
00:02:27,393 --> 00:02:28,428
( Von Stroheim gasps )

48
00:02:28,494 --> 00:02:31,097
( man vocalizing )

49
00:02:31,164 --> 00:02:33,266
♪

50
00:02:38,171 --> 00:02:39,640
( JoJo shudders )

51
00:02:42,509 --> 00:02:44,645
( sizzling )

52
00:02:47,313 --> 00:02:48,481
( gasps )

53
00:02:48,515 --> 00:02:51,251
( screams )

54
00:02:51,317 --> 00:02:54,187
( Von Stroheim shuddering )

55
00:02:54,287 --> 00:02:55,622
( JoJo groaning )

56
00:02:55,689 --> 00:02:57,524
( screams )

57
00:02:57,591 --> 00:02:58,659
( Kars chuckles )

58
00:02:58,692 --> 00:03:01,201
MUSIC TO MY EARS.

59
00:03:01,301 --> 00:03:04,204
YOU PERFORM THAT ARIA PERFECTLY.

60
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:07,508
I'VE SO LONGED
TO HEAR YOU SING IT, JOJO.

61
00:03:07,541 --> 00:03:09,042
( JoJo groaning )

62
00:03:09,109 --> 00:03:12,646
Von Stroheim:
KARS, YOU'RE ALIVE.

63
00:03:13,714 --> 00:03:15,315
A BIT OF HIS SHELL.

64
00:03:15,381 --> 00:03:16,983
( mechanism whirs )

65
00:03:20,687 --> 00:03:23,323
INORGANIC. BUT OF COURSE.

66
00:03:23,389 --> 00:03:25,125
( Kars chuckles )

67
00:03:25,191 --> 00:03:26,860
Narrator:
KARS FIRST COVERED HIMSELF

68
00:03:26,893 --> 00:03:29,730
IN A SUBSTANCE
NOT UNLIKE A CRAB SHELL.

69
00:03:29,796 --> 00:03:32,733
HOWEVER, IT WAS STILL ORGANIC.

70
00:03:32,799 --> 00:03:34,300
IT WASN'T UP TO THE TASK.

71
00:03:34,367 --> 00:03:39,039
FACED WITH THE HEAT OF THE LAVA,
IT BURNED AWAY INSTANTLY.

72
00:03:39,072 --> 00:03:40,674
LUCKILY FOR KARS,

73
00:03:40,741 --> 00:03:44,210
HE HAD THE IDEA TO CREATE
A SECOND LAYER OF ARMOR

74
00:03:44,244 --> 00:03:47,147
MADE OF AN UNLIKELY SUBSTANCE,

75
00:03:47,213 --> 00:03:50,150
‐ MERE AIR BUBBLES.
‐ ( Kars chuckles )

76
00:03:50,216 --> 00:03:52,686
Narrator: THE BUBBLES MAINTAINED
A POCKET OF AIR

77
00:03:52,753 --> 00:03:55,088
BETWEEN KARS'S BODY
AND THE LETHAL HEAT.

78
00:03:55,155 --> 00:03:58,091
AS THE OUTER LAYER BURNED AWAY
WITH EACH PASSING SECOND,

79
00:03:58,191 --> 00:04:00,934
MORE BUBBLES WORKED THEIR WAY
OUTWARD TO REPLACE THEM,

80
00:04:01,034 --> 00:04:02,669
MAINTAINING
A PERFECT EQUILIBRIUM.

81
00:04:02,736 --> 00:04:06,840
KARS HAD THE MOMENTS
HE NEEDED TO ESCAPE.

82
00:04:08,942 --> 00:04:11,578
THE EARTH GAVE BIRTH TO LIFE,

83
00:04:11,612 --> 00:04:13,947
BUT NOW, HORROR OF HORRORS,

84
00:04:14,047 --> 00:04:16,382
KARS, A CREATURE OF THE EARTH,

85
00:04:16,449 --> 00:04:18,919
HAS CONQUERED THE PLANET ITSELF.

86
00:04:18,952 --> 00:04:21,021
♪

87
00:04:21,087 --> 00:04:25,892
EONS AGO, LONG BEFORE MAN FIRST
THOUGHT TO CHRONICLE HIS DEEDS,

88
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:28,929
A GROUP OF CREATURES,
LIKE US, BUT NOT,

89
00:04:28,962 --> 00:04:31,364
EVOLVED ALONGSIDE HUMANITY.

90
00:04:31,431 --> 00:04:33,233
THE SUN WAS LETHAL TO THEM,

91
00:04:33,299 --> 00:04:37,704
SO THEY LIVED OUT THEIR LIVES
UNDER THE COOL GLOW OF THE MOON

92
00:04:37,771 --> 00:04:40,641
AND IN THEIR
SUBTERRANEAN CITIES.

93
00:04:40,707 --> 00:04:43,877
EVEN WITHOUT
THE SUN'S SUSTAINING RAYS,

94
00:04:43,944 --> 00:04:46,813
THEY ENDURED FAR LONGER
THAN THEIR HUMAN RIVALS

95
00:04:46,913 --> 00:04:49,149
BY FEEDING
ON OTHER LIVING THINGS.

96
00:04:49,249 --> 00:04:51,785
TO HUMANS THAT KNEW
OF THEIR EXISTENCE,

97
00:04:51,818 --> 00:04:55,255
THEY WERE REVERED
AS GODS OR DEMONS.

98
00:04:55,321 --> 00:04:57,057
THEIR NUMBERS WERE SMALL,

99
00:04:57,123 --> 00:04:59,325
AS FEW DIED
AND CHILDREN WERE RARE.

100
00:04:59,392 --> 00:05:02,836
IN ALL THINGS,
THEY MAINTAINED A VITAL BALANCE.

101
00:05:02,936 --> 00:05:07,674
THEY KNEW NO STRIFE AND LIVED
IN PEACE WITH ONE ANOTHER.

102
00:05:07,741 --> 00:05:09,009
BUT THEN...

103
00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:13,747
A MAN OF GREAT PRIDE AND
AMBITION WAS BORN AMONG THEM.

104
00:05:15,949 --> 00:05:18,852
Kars: STRENGTH IS HIDDEN
WITHIN THIS BODY,

105
00:05:18,919 --> 00:05:21,755
TALENTS WE CAN
NAUGHT BUT DREAM OF.

106
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:24,758
I SHALL BE THE ONE
TO UNLOCK THEM.

107
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:28,929
Narrator: TO THAT END,
HE CREATED A STONE MASK.

108
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:32,999
THE MASK GRANTED HIM
UNHERALDED POWER,

109
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:36,036
BUT AT A TERRIBLE,
RAVENOUS COST.

110
00:05:36,136 --> 00:05:39,806
TO SURVIVE, HE HAD TO CONSUME
LIFE AT A DIZZYING RATE.

111
00:05:39,873 --> 00:05:41,274
IF LEFT UNCHECKED,

112
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:44,177
HE WOULD EVENTUALLY DEVOUR
EVERY LIVING THING ON EARTH.

113
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:47,047
HIS BRETHREN
BEGAN TO FEAR THE MASK,

114
00:05:47,113 --> 00:05:50,216
AS WELL AS THE GIFTED SOUL
WHO CREATED IT.

115
00:05:50,283 --> 00:05:51,217
Kars: HMM?

116
00:05:51,284 --> 00:05:53,720
Male: HIS VERY EXISTENCE
IS A THREAT!

117
00:05:53,787 --> 00:05:54,955
Male #2: THERE IS NO PLACE

118
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:56,857
FOR ONE SUCH AS HIM
IN THIS WORLD.

119
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,492
Female: AHH!
WE HAVE TO WIPE OUT HIS EVIL.

120
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,134
Kars: LOOK AT YOU FOOLS.

121
00:06:01,201 --> 00:06:04,571
DON'T YOU WANT
TO HAVE DOMINION OVER THE SUN?

122
00:06:04,671 --> 00:06:08,008
TO STAND IN ASCENDANCE
OVER ALL LIFE?

123
00:06:08,074 --> 00:06:12,012
TO PURGE YOUR FEARS
AND REIGN FOREVER AS GODS?

124
00:06:12,078 --> 00:06:15,582
♪

125
00:06:15,682 --> 00:06:18,585
IF NOT, THEN DIE.

126
00:06:18,685 --> 00:06:20,253
( all yelling )

127
00:06:25,391 --> 00:06:26,927
Narrator: THE ICONOCLAST

128
00:06:27,027 --> 00:06:29,029
BRAZENLY SLAUGHTERED
HIS BRETHREN,

129
00:06:29,095 --> 00:06:32,232
EVEN KILLING THE PARENTS
WHO HAD GIVEN HIM LIFE.

130
00:06:33,266 --> 00:06:34,935
HE AND HIS SOLE ALLY

131
00:06:35,001 --> 00:06:36,737
TOOK THE TWO SURVIVING INFANTS

132
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:39,072
AND LEFT THE SCENE
OF THE CARNAGE.

133
00:06:39,105 --> 00:06:41,708
THEY SET OFF
IN SEARCH OF ULTIMATE POWER,

134
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:44,678
A JOURNEY OF CONTINENTS
AND CENTURIES ALIKE.

135
00:06:44,745 --> 00:06:47,280
AND NOW,
TEN THOUSAND YEARS LATER,

136
00:06:47,347 --> 00:06:50,216
THAT POWER WAS
IN HIS HANDS AT LAST.

137
00:06:52,753 --> 00:06:54,220
Von Stroheim: HE'S A GOD.

138
00:06:54,287 --> 00:06:56,957
THIS TYRANT HAS BECOME A DEITY,

139
00:06:57,057 --> 00:07:01,434
AND AGAINST SUCH A FOE,
THERE IS NOTHING THAT WE CAN DO.

140
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:04,605
WE MUST SUBMIT OR PERISH!

141
00:07:04,638 --> 00:07:07,207
( JoJo groaning )

142
00:07:07,273 --> 00:07:08,308
Kars: HMM?

143
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:10,811
HEAR THAT?

144
00:07:10,877 --> 00:07:14,414
I THINK JOJO IS TRYING
TO TELL ME SOMETHING.

145
00:07:17,417 --> 00:07:21,655
JoJo: HAMON OVERDRIVE!

146
00:07:21,722 --> 00:07:24,157
Kars: WHAT? HAMON?

147
00:07:25,158 --> 00:07:27,828
DID YOU SAY, "HAMON OVERDRIVE"?!

148
00:07:27,928 --> 00:07:30,764
( JoJo screams )

149
00:07:30,831 --> 00:07:31,965
Von Stroheim: JOJO!

150
00:07:31,998 --> 00:07:33,333
( Kars scoffs )

151
00:07:34,501 --> 00:07:37,604
( JoJo gasps )
NO. HOW?

152
00:07:37,671 --> 00:07:40,641
MY LEG, IT'S MELTING AWAY.

153
00:07:40,674 --> 00:07:42,442
THIS IS IMPOSSIBLE!

154
00:07:42,509 --> 00:07:44,945
Von Stroheim: MELTING?
YOU DON'T MEAN TO SAY...

155
00:07:45,011 --> 00:07:46,246
JoJo: IT CAN'T BE!

156
00:07:46,312 --> 00:07:49,816
Kars: DENIAL WILL GET YOU
NOWHERE, MY FRIEND.

157
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:51,618
HAMON DID THAT.

158
00:07:51,685 --> 00:07:54,020
I CONQUERED THE SUN ITSELF.

159
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,189
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
THAT SOMETHING LIKE HAMON

160
00:07:56,256 --> 00:07:57,958
WAS SOMEHOW BEYOND MY REACH?

161
00:07:58,024 --> 00:07:59,259
JoJo: HUH? I JUST...

162
00:07:59,325 --> 00:08:01,635
Kars: NOT ONLY
IS HAMON AT MY DISPOSAL,

163
00:08:01,702 --> 00:08:05,105
BUT IT SEEMS THAT MINE IS
HUNDREDS OF TIMES MORE POTENT.

164
00:08:05,171 --> 00:08:08,509
Von Stroheim: MEIN GOTT.
THAT MUCH STRONGER THAN JOJO'S?

165
00:08:08,542 --> 00:08:12,378
IT'S AS THOUGH HE BRUSHED
HIS KNEE AGAINST THE SUN.

166
00:08:12,445 --> 00:08:15,882
HIS FLESH IS LIQUEFYING
UND VAPORIZING

167
00:08:15,949 --> 00:08:17,483
BEFORE HIS VERY EYES.

168
00:08:17,551 --> 00:08:21,387
Kars: I WONDER, HOW DO YOU LIKE
THE TASTE OF YOUR OWN MEDICINE?

169
00:08:21,454 --> 00:08:22,989
( JoJo groaning )

170
00:08:23,056 --> 00:08:27,193
Kars: HMM.
A VERY ARTICULATE REPLY.

171
00:08:28,128 --> 00:08:29,796
Kars: I SUPPOSE IT'S TIME

172
00:08:29,863 --> 00:08:31,965
TO PUT YOU OUT OF YOUR MISERY.

173
00:08:32,032 --> 00:08:33,166
Von Stroheim: JOJO!

174
00:08:35,001 --> 00:08:38,672
JoJo: THIS IS IT.
I'M GOING TO DIE HERE.

175
00:08:38,739 --> 00:08:41,074
THIS IS THE END.

176
00:08:41,174 --> 00:08:44,210
Narrator: JOJO ACCEPTED
HIS IMPENDING DEMISE CALMLY.

177
00:08:44,244 --> 00:08:48,882
HE FELT NO FEAR, NO PAIN,
NO REGRET AT HIS PLIGHT.

178
00:08:48,915 --> 00:08:51,417
"I DID ALL I COULD,"
HE TOLD HIMSELF.

179
00:08:51,484 --> 00:08:55,922
AS THE EPITOME OF EVIL
LOOMED OVER JOJO IN TRIUMPH,

180
00:08:56,022 --> 00:08:59,593
HE WATCHED HIS DYING SELF
WITH PERFECT CLARITY.

181
00:08:59,693 --> 00:09:02,202
STROHEIM FELT MUCH THE SAME.

182
00:09:02,268 --> 00:09:06,106
UNABLE TO MOVE, HE KNEW
WHAT SNAKE PREY FELLS LIKE

183
00:09:06,172 --> 00:09:09,009
AS IT STARES
INTO OBLIVION'S MAW.

184
00:09:09,075 --> 00:09:13,279
( Kars breathes deeply )

185
00:09:13,346 --> 00:09:16,282
THE POWER IN A BREATH.
( chuckles )

186
00:09:16,349 --> 00:09:20,186
TO THINK I WILL ANNIHILATE
A PRACTITIONER OF HAMON

187
00:09:20,253 --> 00:09:22,288
WITH HIS OWN DISCIPLINE.

188
00:09:22,355 --> 00:09:24,290
♪

189
00:09:25,959 --> 00:09:30,564
SURELY YOU CAN APPRECIATE
THE IRONY IN THAT.

190
00:09:30,631 --> 00:09:33,867
JoJo: HA...MON...

191
00:09:33,934 --> 00:09:35,035
( Kars yelling )

192
00:09:35,101 --> 00:09:37,638
JoJo: STRONGER THAN MINE
HAS EVER BEEN.

193
00:09:37,704 --> 00:09:42,643
Kars: LET ME BE THE FIRST
TO WELCOME YOU INTO OBLIVION!

194
00:09:42,743 --> 00:09:45,045
JoJo: WAIT. HAMON.

195
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:50,817
( Von Stroheim gasps )

196
00:09:50,884 --> 00:09:52,052
Kars: WHAT THE...

197
00:09:53,419 --> 00:09:55,155
THE RED STONE!

198
00:10:01,318 --> 00:10:02,769
Kars: WHAT THE...

199
00:10:02,836 --> 00:10:04,505
THE RED STONE!

200
00:10:08,374 --> 00:10:10,443
Narrator: THE RED STONE OF AJA.

201
00:10:10,511 --> 00:10:13,113
BUT WHY DID JOJO
BRANDISH IT AT KARS

202
00:10:13,179 --> 00:10:16,282
IN THAT FINAL MOMENT?
EVEN HE HAD NO IDEA.

203
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:18,885
AS IF BY INSTINCT,

204
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:20,286
HE'D LUNGED THE STONE

205
00:10:20,386 --> 00:10:23,924
TOWARDS THE APPROACHING HAMON
TO WHICH IT GRAVITATED.

206
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,860
( singing in Japanese )

207
00:10:26,927 --> 00:10:29,395
NOW IN A MOMENT DEVOID OF HOPE,

208
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:32,599
JOJO'S BODY DID THE ONE THING
THAT COULD SAVE HIS LIFE.

209
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:35,135
HAVING SURVIVED
KAR'S COUP DE GRACE,

210
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:37,538
HIS WILL TO LIVE
SPRANG INTO ACTION.

211
00:10:37,604 --> 00:10:42,142
JoJo: YES. THE RED STONE
AMPLIFIES HAMON.

212
00:10:43,376 --> 00:10:44,477
Kars: HUH?

213
00:10:44,545 --> 00:10:46,079
( gasps )

214
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:49,115
Narrator: FUELED BY
THE MAGNIFIED BLAST OF HAMON,

215
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:51,317
THE VOLCANO'S FURY
REACHES THE BREAKING POINT.

216
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:53,053
IT ERUPTS!

217
00:10:53,119 --> 00:10:54,320
( Von Stroheim yells )

218
00:10:54,387 --> 00:10:56,256
♪

219
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:03,336
WHAT? THEY BLASTED INTO THE SKY!

220
00:11:03,436 --> 00:11:06,172
♪

221
00:11:06,239 --> 00:11:07,974
‐ ( JoJo groaning )
‐ ( singing in Japanese )

222
00:11:08,008 --> 00:11:10,443
Kars: THE FORCE, IT'S STRONG,

223
00:11:10,511 --> 00:11:12,913
LIKE NOTHING I'VE EVER KNOWN.

224
00:11:12,979 --> 00:11:16,016
♪

225
00:11:17,283 --> 00:11:19,352
DO YOU REALLY THINK
A LITTLE ERUPTION

226
00:11:19,419 --> 00:11:22,355
WILL BE ENOUGH TO CONQUER
THE LIKES OF ME?!

227
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:26,492
I'LL JUST FLY MY WAY TO SAFETY.

228
00:11:26,527 --> 00:11:30,597
ENJOY THE FRUITS
OF YOUR FOLLY, JOJO.

229
00:11:30,664 --> 00:11:32,365
( gags )

230
00:11:32,432 --> 00:11:34,801
JoJo: WHO'S LAUGHING NOW, HUH?

231
00:11:37,871 --> 00:11:39,806
LET ME GUESS.

232
00:11:39,873 --> 00:11:43,877
YOU'RE GONNA SAY, "DID YOU
PLAN THIS, TOO, JOJO? TELL ME."

233
00:11:43,944 --> 00:11:45,612
Kars: HOW DO YOU ALWAYS KNOW?

234
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:48,314
Narrator: FOR A MOMENT,
KARS WAS DISTRACTED

235
00:11:48,381 --> 00:11:50,817
BY JOJO'S ARM
AND HIS COCKY ATTITUDE.

236
00:11:50,884 --> 00:11:52,953
THAT MOMENT WAS ALL IT TOOK.

237
00:11:53,019 --> 00:11:55,556
SCALDING ROCKS
HE DIDN'T SEE COMING

238
00:11:55,622 --> 00:11:58,024
LAUNCHED HIM EVEN HIGHER
INTO THE STRATOSPHERE.

239
00:11:58,058 --> 00:11:59,893
( Kars screams )

240
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:02,636
DID YOU PLAN THIS, TOO, JOJO!

241
00:12:02,703 --> 00:12:03,737
TELL ME!

242
00:12:03,804 --> 00:12:05,405
JoJo: WHY ARE YOU EVEN ASKING?!

243
00:12:05,471 --> 00:12:08,575
I SET THE TRAP,
AND YOU WALKED RIGHT INTO IT!

244
00:12:08,642 --> 00:12:11,044
ALL OF THIS WENT DOWN
LIKE CLOCKWORK.

245
00:12:11,077 --> 00:12:13,413
( Kars screams )

246
00:12:14,681 --> 00:12:16,249
JoJo: I JUST GOT LUCKY,

247
00:12:16,349 --> 00:12:18,919
BUT THINKING I OUTSMARTED HIM
WILL DRIVE KARS NUTS.

248
00:12:19,019 --> 00:12:20,220
( laughs )

249
00:12:20,253 --> 00:12:22,255
Narrator: AT THAT MOMENT,
THE ROCKS LAUNCHED

250
00:12:22,355 --> 00:12:26,026
BY THE VOLCANO'S ERUPTION
REACHED ESCAPE VELOCITY.

251
00:12:26,092 --> 00:12:27,994
KARS WAS THE PERFECT BEING.

252
00:12:28,061 --> 00:12:29,763
NOTHING ON EARTH COULD KILL HIM,

253
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:31,565
BUT JUST THEN...

254
00:12:31,598 --> 00:12:35,268
HE WAS BLASTED
INTO THE VACUUM OF SPACE.

255
00:12:35,368 --> 00:12:38,171
Kars: NO! DAMN YOU!

256
00:12:38,238 --> 00:12:45,178
Singer: ♪ JOJO

257
00:12:45,245 --> 00:12:46,379
( music ends )

258
00:12:46,446 --> 00:12:47,714
JoJo: IT'S OVER.

259
00:12:48,782 --> 00:12:52,185
GRANNY AND STROHEIM,

260
00:12:52,252 --> 00:12:56,122
OLD SPEEDWAGON, SMOKEY...

261
00:12:57,223 --> 00:13:00,801
AND LISA LISA.

262
00:13:00,867 --> 00:13:04,137
EVERYONE, GOODBYE.

263
00:13:07,641 --> 00:13:08,575
Von Stroheim: NO.

264
00:13:09,643 --> 00:13:13,814
JOJO!

265
00:13:13,914 --> 00:13:15,982
Narrator: VON STROHEIM
MADE IT BACK TO THE OTHERS

266
00:13:16,049 --> 00:13:20,153
EIGHT HOURS LATER, WHEREUPON
HE TOLD THEM THE SAD NEWS.

267
00:13:31,965 --> 00:13:32,899
Kars: NO!

268
00:13:32,966 --> 00:13:35,001
THE EARTH! NO!

269
00:13:35,101 --> 00:13:36,269
DON'T PANIC.

270
00:13:36,336 --> 00:13:37,938
JUST FIND THE EARTH.

271
00:13:41,407 --> 00:13:43,844
I'LL USE AIR
TO CHANGE MY TRAJECTORY.

272
00:13:43,944 --> 00:13:48,248
ONCE I'M BACK ON SOLID GROUND,
I WILL TEAR THAT BOY APART.

273
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:58,925
( groans )

274
00:14:01,802 --> 00:14:03,937
( screaming )

275
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:10,143
NO! IT'S NOT WORKING!

276
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:12,946
I'M FREEZING.

277
00:14:13,013 --> 00:14:15,682
THE AIR IS FREEZING AROUND ME.

278
00:14:15,716 --> 00:14:19,986
THE MOMENT IT COMES OUT
OF THE JETS, IT TURNS TO ICE.

279
00:14:23,356 --> 00:14:26,192
I CAN'T CHANGE MY PATH.

280
00:14:26,226 --> 00:14:28,829
I CAN'T MOVE.

281
00:14:28,895 --> 00:14:32,332
( screams )

282
00:14:33,867 --> 00:14:36,136
Narrator: SO ENDED KARS,

283
00:14:36,202 --> 00:14:38,572
LAST AND GREATEST
OF THE PILLAR MEN.

284
00:14:38,639 --> 00:14:41,374
HIS BODY TURNED HARD AS ROCK,

285
00:14:41,407 --> 00:14:44,711
AND HE FLOATED THROUGH SPACE
FOR THE REST OF TIME,

286
00:14:44,745 --> 00:14:47,313
NEVER TO RETURN.

287
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:48,749
HE WISHED FOR DEATH,

288
00:14:48,849 --> 00:14:51,084
BUT THERE WAS NOTHING OUT THERE
TO KILL HIM.

289
00:14:51,184 --> 00:14:57,023
THE SPARK OF THOUGHT WITHIN HIM
WENT DIM AND THEN SILENT.

290
00:14:59,826 --> 00:15:01,768
( bell tolling )

291
00:15:01,835 --> 00:15:03,770
♪

292
00:15:06,673 --> 00:15:10,611
Priest: WE COMMEND HIS SOUL
UNTO THE HEAVENLY FATHER.

293
00:15:10,677 --> 00:15:14,414
THOUGH HIS LIFE ON EARTH
HAS ENDED FAR TOO SOON,

294
00:15:14,447 --> 00:15:16,750
HE LIVES IN GRACE WITH YOU.

295
00:15:16,783 --> 00:15:20,086
COMFORT THOSE
HE LEAVES BEHIND, O GOD,

296
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,222
AND LET THEM KNOW YOUR PEACE.

297
00:15:22,288 --> 00:15:24,424
♪

298
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:36,603
Smokey: GOODBYE, JOJO.

299
00:15:36,637 --> 00:15:38,805
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU FOR TOO LONG.

300
00:15:38,872 --> 00:15:41,407
COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
MORE THAN SIX MONTHS.

301
00:15:43,577 --> 00:15:45,145
DON'T MATTER.

302
00:15:45,245 --> 00:15:46,980
EVEN THOUGH YOU'RE GONE,

303
00:15:47,047 --> 00:15:48,081
I'M YOUR FRIEND...

304
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:50,984
FOREVER.

305
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:59,560
Speedwagon: COME, ERINA.
IT WON'T DO TO CATCH COLD.

306
00:15:59,626 --> 00:16:01,602
LET'S GET YOU HOME.

307
00:16:01,668 --> 00:16:03,504
Erina: JUST A BIT LONGER.

308
00:16:06,573 --> 00:16:08,074
( JoJo laughs )

309
00:16:08,141 --> 00:16:10,176
GUESS WHO.

310
00:16:10,243 --> 00:16:11,477
( Lisa Lisa gasps )

311
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:13,179
JoJo: WHAT GIVES, FELLAS?

312
00:16:13,246 --> 00:16:15,448
I FINALLY MAKE IT TO NEW YORK,

313
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:17,684
AND NOBODY WAS THERE
TO PICK ME UP.

314
00:16:17,784 --> 00:16:20,954
THEN I GOT WORD
YOU WERE ALL AT A FUNERAL,

315
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:22,523
SO I DECIDED TO CRASH IT.

316
00:16:22,623 --> 00:16:24,591
‐ ( both gasp )
‐ JoJo: HEY, LISA LISA.

317
00:16:24,658 --> 00:16:27,027
GUESS YOU HEALED UP
PRETTY WELL, HUH?

318
00:16:27,127 --> 00:16:28,962
MESHINA, GOOD TO SEE YOU, TOO.

319
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,030
NEW HAND WORKS WELL,

320
00:16:30,130 --> 00:16:32,465
THOUGH I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO ASK STROHEIM

321
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:33,834
IF HE CAN JAZZ IT UP

322
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,802
WITH A FEW GADGETS
OR TOOLS OR WHATNOT.

323
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:39,540
I GUESS THAT'S RIGHT OUT,
WITH US FIGHTING GERMANY.

324
00:16:39,606 --> 00:16:42,042
Man: HEY, NOW.
YOU LEAVE THESE MOURNERS ALONE.

325
00:16:42,142 --> 00:16:45,278
Man #2: THIS IS A FUNERAL.
SHOW SOME RESPECT, YOU OAF.

326
00:16:45,345 --> 00:16:47,047
JoJo: OH, SO I'M AN OAF, AM I?

327
00:16:47,113 --> 00:16:50,050
YOU NEED A LESSON IN MANNERS,
AND I'M GLAD TO OBLIGE.

328
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:53,386
Man #1: ALL RIGHT.
CALM DOWN. LET'S NOT BE HASTY.

329
00:16:53,486 --> 00:16:55,388
‐ Meshina: BUT HOW?
‐ ( argument continues )

330
00:16:55,488 --> 00:16:56,823
‐ Smokey: NO WAY.
‐ Man #1: HEY,

331
00:16:56,890 --> 00:17:00,026
I'M TALKING TO YOU, BIG GUY.
YOU'D BETTER‐‐

332
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,367
JoJo: BACK OFF, MAN!

333
00:17:01,401 --> 00:17:04,370
I'M JUST TRYING TO CATCH UP
WITH MY FAMILY AND FRIENDS.

334
00:17:04,404 --> 00:17:05,839
All: JOJO!

335
00:17:05,906 --> 00:17:06,807
( Smokey screams )

336
00:17:06,873 --> 00:17:09,142
YOU'RE TELLING ME JOJO'S ALIVE?!

337
00:17:09,209 --> 00:17:11,244
JoJo: HUH? YEAH, OF COURSE.

338
00:17:11,311 --> 00:17:12,746
WAIT. WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

339
00:17:12,846 --> 00:17:15,248
YOU'RE ALL STARING
AS THOUGH YOU'VE SEEN A GHOST.

340
00:17:15,348 --> 00:17:17,083
I KNOW IT'S A FUNERAL AND A‐‐

341
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:18,084
HUH?

342
00:17:19,152 --> 00:17:20,587
WHAT THE?!

343
00:17:20,687 --> 00:17:22,823
WHAT'S MY NAME DOING ON THERE?
I'M ALIVE AND WELL!

344
00:17:22,889 --> 00:17:24,490
WAIT. THIS FUNERAL WAS FOR ME?

345
00:17:24,558 --> 00:17:25,726
Suzie Q: JOJO!

346
00:17:25,759 --> 00:17:28,562
YOU'RE STILL RECOVERING,
YOU BIG SILLY.

347
00:17:28,595 --> 00:17:31,064
DON'T RUN OFF IN THE RAIN
LIKE THAT.

348
00:17:31,097 --> 00:17:34,500
( all gasp )

349
00:17:34,568 --> 00:17:36,169
Suzie Q: HERE. TAKE THIS.

350
00:17:37,437 --> 00:17:39,706
Meshina: HEY,
THAT GIRL IS SUZIE Q,

351
00:17:39,773 --> 00:17:42,275
AND THAT‐‐THAT RING
LOOKS LIKE A...

352
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:43,910
( JoJo gags )
ARE YOU TELLING ME

353
00:17:43,944 --> 00:17:46,112
YOU DON'T KNOW
THAT WE GOT MARRIED?

354
00:17:46,212 --> 00:17:47,914
All: YOU GOT MARRIED?

355
00:17:47,948 --> 00:17:50,951
Suzie Q: ISN'T IT CRAZY?
JUST THINK ABOUT IT.

356
00:17:51,051 --> 00:17:55,789
I'M OFFICIALLY
MRS. JOSEPH JOESTAR. GOODNESS.

357
00:17:55,889 --> 00:17:57,090
( squeals )

358
00:17:57,123 --> 00:17:59,425
IT MAKES ME BLUSH.

359
00:17:59,459 --> 00:18:02,035
‐ ( sighs )
‐ JoJo: WAIT A SECOND HERE.

360
00:18:02,102 --> 00:18:05,138
SUZIE Q, SOMETHING ABOUT THIS
DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT,

361
00:18:05,205 --> 00:18:06,640
AND I WANNA KNOW WHAT.

362
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:09,610
THE ROCK I WAS ON
FELL INTO THE OCEAN,

363
00:18:09,643 --> 00:18:10,744
AND ME ALONG WITH IT.

364
00:18:10,811 --> 00:18:12,378
A FISHING BOAT PICKED ME UP.

365
00:18:12,445 --> 00:18:14,280
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

366
00:18:14,314 --> 00:18:17,050
YOU NURSED ME BACK TO HEALTH
IN VENICE FOR TWO WEEKS,

367
00:18:17,117 --> 00:18:18,652
AND WE TIED THE KNOT.

368
00:18:18,719 --> 00:18:22,255
SO WHY DID THEY
ALL THINK I WAS DEAD?

369
00:18:22,322 --> 00:18:25,826
YOU NEVER SENT THAT TELEGRAM
LIKE I ASKED, DID YOU?!

370
00:18:25,892 --> 00:18:28,629
Suzie Q: UH,
I DON'T REALLY KNOW.

371
00:18:28,662 --> 00:18:31,097
JoJo: TO ME,
THAT SOUNDS LIKE NO!

372
00:18:31,164 --> 00:18:33,433
Suzie Q: UH...

373
00:18:33,499 --> 00:18:35,001
( machinery clicking )

374
00:18:35,101 --> 00:18:39,072
NOW, NOW. LET'S NOT GET
ALL CLICKY‐FINGERS.

375
00:18:39,139 --> 00:18:40,574
I NEVER SENT IT!

376
00:18:40,641 --> 00:18:42,809
‐ I'M SORRY, JOJO!
‐ ( JoJo groans )

377
00:18:42,843 --> 00:18:44,945
SUZIE Q, WHAT THE HELL?!

378
00:18:45,011 --> 00:18:47,581
YOU HAD ONE JOB, WOMAN,
ONE JOB!

379
00:18:47,648 --> 00:18:49,415
‐ ( Suzie Q squeals )
‐ ( Smokey sobs )

380
00:18:49,482 --> 00:18:52,853
JOJO CAME BACK TO US ALL!

381
00:18:52,919 --> 00:18:54,688
Suzie Q: STOP IT!
I SAID I WAS SORRY!

382
00:18:54,788 --> 00:18:57,524
JoJo: SORRY?!
THEY THOUGHT I WAS DEAD!

383
00:18:58,692 --> 00:19:00,160
Lisa Lisa: JOJO.

384
00:19:00,193 --> 00:19:04,437
Narrator: SOON AFTER, LISA LISA,
A. K. A. ELIZABETH JOESTAR,

385
00:19:04,505 --> 00:19:06,540
TOLD JOJO
THAT SHE WAS HIS MOTHER.

386
00:19:06,607 --> 00:19:09,342
THEY MOVED TO AMERICA.

387
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:12,846
IN 1948, SHE FOUND LOVE AGAIN

388
00:19:12,879 --> 00:19:15,348
AND MARRIED
A HOLLYWOOD SCREENWRITER.

389
00:19:15,381 --> 00:19:17,718
( Erina sighs )

390
00:19:17,818 --> 00:19:21,154
Narrator: ERINA JOESTAR
CONTINUED HER WORK AS A TEACHER.

391
00:19:21,221 --> 00:19:25,959
IN 1950, SHE DIED PEACEFULLY
AT THE AGE OF 81,

392
00:19:26,026 --> 00:19:30,396
SURROUNDED BY FAMILY AND FRIENDS
WHO LOVED HER.

393
00:19:30,463 --> 00:19:31,965
( Speedwagon chuckles )

394
00:19:32,032 --> 00:19:34,968
Narrator:
ROBERT E. O. SPEEDWAGON

395
00:19:35,035 --> 00:19:38,238
CONTINUED TO POUR HIS ENERGY
INTO PHILANTHROPIC RESEARCH,

396
00:19:38,304 --> 00:19:41,575
HELPING TO FURTHER SCIENCE
AND MEDICINE IN COUNTLESS WAYS.

397
00:19:41,642 --> 00:19:44,745
HE DIED IN 1952
OF A HEART ATTACK

398
00:19:44,845 --> 00:19:46,146
AT 89 YEARS OF AGE.

399
00:19:46,212 --> 00:19:50,016
A LIFELONG BACHELOR,
HE LEFT NO FAMILY BEHIND.

400
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:53,520
SMOKEY BROWN WENT ON
TO WORK HIS WAY THROUGH COLLEGE,

401
00:19:53,587 --> 00:19:55,989
MAJORING IN POLITICAL SCIENCE.

402
00:19:57,190 --> 00:20:00,326
LATER, HE BECAME
THE FIRST BLACK MAYOR OF A CITY

403
00:20:00,393 --> 00:20:02,102
IN HIS HOME STATE OF GEORGIA.

404
00:20:03,469 --> 00:20:04,871
MAJOR RUDOL VON STROHEIM

405
00:20:04,971 --> 00:20:07,173
WOULD NEVER SEE JOJO AGAIN.

406
00:20:07,207 --> 00:20:10,544
HE DIED IN 1943
AT THE BATTLE OF STALINGRAD,

407
00:20:10,611 --> 00:20:12,546
A FEARSOME EXAMPLE

408
00:20:12,646 --> 00:20:14,781
OF THE GERMAN SCIENCE
HE'D ALWAYS CHAMPIONED.

409
00:20:14,848 --> 00:20:17,784
Von Stroheim: OUR TECHNOLOGY
IS THE GREATEST!

410
00:20:17,851 --> 00:20:19,786
♪

411
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:28,194
Narrator: AND SO
THE YEARS FLOWED BY...

412
00:20:28,228 --> 00:20:31,331
TO A NEW GENERATION.

413
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:32,966
AND AS FOR JOJO...

414
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,369
( JoJo groans )

415
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,404
Man: OH. RIGHT IN THE LEG, HUH?

416
00:20:38,471 --> 00:20:39,673
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

417
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:41,141
YOU SHOULD WATCH
WHERE YOU'RE GOING.

418
00:20:41,207 --> 00:20:43,577
YOU WOULDN'T WANT
A BROKEN BONE AT YOUR AGE.

419
00:20:43,644 --> 00:20:45,912
JoJo: YOU'RE RIGHT.
HOW CARELESS OF ME.

420
00:20:45,979 --> 00:20:48,849
I GUESS THIS IS A CASE
OF LIVE AND LEARN.

421
00:20:48,915 --> 00:20:50,584
HMM? HEY, WAIT A SEC.

422
00:20:50,684 --> 00:20:52,653
YOU'RE JAPANESE, AREN'T YOU?

423
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:54,087
Man: I AM. WHY DO YOU ASK?

424
00:20:54,154 --> 00:20:57,591
JoJo: IN THAT CASE,
WATCH YOUR DAMN BAG!

425
00:20:57,691 --> 00:20:59,392
Man: YOW!

426
00:20:59,425 --> 00:21:00,534
( JoJo scoffs )

427
00:21:00,601 --> 00:21:01,768
( man groaning )

428
00:21:01,835 --> 00:21:04,605
Announcer:
ALITALIA FLIGHT 285 FOR TOKYO

429
00:21:04,671 --> 00:21:06,940
IS NOW BOARDING
OUT OF GATE C‐17.

430
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:07,941
( JoJo cries )

431
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:10,043
MY ONLY DAUGHTER
HAS BEEN MARRIED

432
00:21:10,110 --> 00:21:12,613
TO A JAPANESE MAN
FOR OVER 20 YEARS,

433
00:21:12,713 --> 00:21:15,616
FELL IN LOVE ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE WORLD,

434
00:21:15,716 --> 00:21:17,083
AND NEVER CAME HOME AGAIN.

435
00:21:17,117 --> 00:21:20,086
HER SON RARELY GETS TO SEE
HIS OWN GRANDFATHER!

436
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:23,590
THAT'S WHY I'LL NEVER
FORGIVE THE JAPANESE!

437
00:21:23,624 --> 00:21:24,725
( man groans )

438
00:21:24,791 --> 00:21:27,060
JoJo: THEN AGAIN...

439
00:21:28,128 --> 00:21:30,864
THEY MAKE
SOME RATHER NIFTY GADGETS.

440
00:21:34,234 --> 00:21:36,136
♪

441
00:21:40,807 --> 00:21:42,976
( singing in Japanese )

442
00:22:49,182 --> 00:22:51,117
♪

443
00:23:05,672 --> 00:23:08,241
( waves lapping )

444
00:23:08,308 --> 00:23:11,712
( man laughs ) ALL RIGHT.
IT'S FINALLY TIME TO HAUL IT UP.

445
00:23:11,745 --> 00:23:15,215
Man #2: OH, MAN. WHAT DO YOU
THINK'S INSIDE IT, YOU GUYS?

446
00:23:15,248 --> 00:23:18,251
Man #1: A HUNDRED‐YEAR‐OLD CHEST
LIKE THAT?

447
00:23:18,318 --> 00:23:19,820
IT COULD BE ANYTHING.

448
00:23:19,886 --> 00:23:23,023
Man #2: COME ON.
LET'S OPEN THAT BAD BOY.

449
00:23:25,091 --> 00:23:27,027
♪

